CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 29, 1964, pg. 12 reads: "Entertained - Some of the youngsters who entertained Cornell Hawkins Bell of Philadelphia, nephew of Miss Maude Y. Hawkins, who has been spending the summer in Pittsburgh. Left to right: Carol Finch, Joseph Finch Jr., Cornell H. Bell, the honoree, and Lynda Branch.  Kneeling in foreground is Susan Finch, holding the dog, Petit Garcon D'Argent. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait from left: Maude Y. Hawkins, holding leash of dog "Petit Garcon D'Argent, " Carol Finch, Joseph Finch Jr., Cornell H. Bell, and Lynda Branch, with Susan Finch in foreground, posed in yard, possibly of Maude Y. Hawkins
